President Trump and First Lady Melania Trump welcomed President Moon Jae-in and Madam Kim Jung-sook of the Republic of Korea (ROK) to the White House. They discussed mutual goals of achieving denuclearization of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) and establishing peace on the Korean Peninsula. President Trump reiterated his good relationship with DPRK Chairman Kim Jong Un and expressed openness to dialogue. They also emphasized the importance of coordination and cooperation on DPRK-related matters. The leaders discussed the strong US-ROK alliance and the positive impact of the United States-Korea Free Trade Agreement on trade between the two countries. They also acknowledged the bravery of Korean first responders in the recent wildfires in the ROK's northeastern province.